segment.source: Applies to
segment.target: Applies to

segment.source: Windows 10
segment.target: Windows 10

segment.source: Windows Server 2016
segment.target: Windows Server 2016

segment.source: Event Description:
segment.target: Event Description:

segment.source: This event generates every time settings from the “Security Settings” section in the group policy object are applied to a computer with one or more errors.
segment.target: This event generates every time settings from the “Security Settings” section in the group policy object are applied to a computer with one or more errors.

segment.source: This event generates on the target computer itself.
segment.target: This event generates on the target computer itself.

segment.source: This event generates, for example, if the SID of a security principal which was included in one of the Group Policy settings cannot be resolved or translated to the real account name.
segment.target: This event generates, for example, if the SID of a security principal which was included in one of the Group Policy settings cannot be resolved or translated to the real account name.

segment.source: Note For recommendations, see Security Monitoring Recommendations for this event.
segment.target: Note For recommendations, see Security Monitoring Recommendations for this event.

segment.source: Event XML:
segment.target: Event XML:

segment.source: Required Server Roles: None.
segment.target: Required Server Roles: None.

segment.source: Minimum OS Version: Windows Server 2008, Windows Vista.
segment.target: Minimum OS Version: Windows Server 2008, Windows Vista.

segment.source: Event Versions: 0.
segment.target: Event Versions: 0.

segment.source: Field Descriptions:
segment.target: Field Descriptions:

segment.source: Error Code Type = UInt32: specific error code which shows the error which happened during Group Policy processing.
segment.target: Error Code Type = UInt32: specific error code which shows the error which happened during Group Policy processing.

segment.source: You can find the meaning of specific error code here: https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms681381(v=vs.85).aspx.
segment.target: You can find the meaning of specific error code here: https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms681381(v=vs.85).aspx.

segment.source: For example, error code 1332 means that “no mapping between account names and security IDs was done”.
segment.target: For example, error code 1332 means that “no mapping between account names and security IDs was done”.

segment.source: GPO List Type = UnicodeString: the list of Group Policy Objects that include “Security Settings” policies, and that were applied with errors to the computer.
segment.target: GPO List Type = UnicodeString: the list of Group Policy Objects that include “Security Settings” policies, and that were applied with errors to the computer.

segment.source: The format of the list item is: “GROUPPOLICYGUID GROUPPOLICYNAME”.
segment.target: The format of the list item is: “GROUPPOLICYGUID GROUPPOLICYNAME”.

segment.source: You can find specific GROUPPOLICYGUID using Get-GPO PowerShell cmdlet with “–Name GROUPPOLICYNAME” parameter.
segment.target: You can find specific GROUPPOLICYGUID using Get-GPO PowerShell cmdlet with “–Name GROUPPOLICYNAME” parameter.

segment.source: Row “Id” is the GUID of the Group Policy:
segment.target: Row “Id” is the GUID of the Group Policy:

GUID is an acronym for 'Globally Unique Identifier'.
segment.target:

segment.source: It is a 128-bit integer number used to identify resources, activities or instances.
segment.target: It is a 128-bit integer number used to identify resources, activities or instances.

segment.source: Security Monitoring Recommendations
segment.target: Security Monitoring Recommendations

segment.source: For 6145(F): One or more errors occurred while processing security policy in the group policy objects.
segment.target: For 6145(F): One or more errors occurred while processing security policy in the group policy objects.

segment.source: This event indicates that Group Policy Objects which were applied to the computer or device had some errors during processing.
segment.target: This event indicates that Group Policy Objects which were applied to the computer or device had some errors during processing.

segment.source: If you see this event, we recommend checking settings in the GPOs from GPO List and resolving the cause of the errors.
segment.target: If you see this event, we recommend checking settings in the GPOs from GPO List and resolving the cause of the errors.

segment.source: If you have a pre-defined list of Group Policy Objects that contain Security Settings and that must be applied to specific computers, check this event to see if errors occurred when the Security Settings were applied.
segment.target: If you have a pre-defined list of Group Policy Objects that contain Security Settings and that must be applied to specific computers, check this event to see if errors occurred when the Security Settings were applied.

segment.source: If so, you can review the error codes and investigate the cause of the failure.
segment.target: If so, you can review the error codes and investigate the cause of the failure.

segment.source: Typically this event has an informational purpose and the reason is configuration errors in Group Policy’s security settings.
segment.target: Typically this event has an informational purpose and the reason is configuration errors in Group Policy’s security settings.

segment.source: This event might be used for Group Policy troubleshooting purposes.
segment.target: This event might be used for Group Policy troubleshooting purposes.
